"reviewcomment":"As the old adage goes location, location, location - that is by far the biggest asset of this hotel and the friendly staff. <br><br>The Warwick is located in front of the train station and pretty close to everything - there is even a shopping mall behind it. The location came in very handy when I was here in February given that it was freezing outside. Many restaurants are a short walk away as are the underground shops of the station.<br><br>The rooms are fairly spacious as are the bathrooms.  The Queen size beds are two small beds put together and if you sleep in the middle as I do you will fall right between the beds. <br><br>The breakfast buffet featured the usual Swiss delights such as Bircher Muessli, eggs, croissants etc - very good. <br><br>For the type of hotel that it is, a slightly older hotel, it&#39;s pretty good. Nice location, good staff - what else does one need.",
