"reviewcomment":"This is a cute, cozy bar serving hearty tapas du pays Basque, wine, and beer, transporting you to the French Basque region. Tapas are served until pretty late - for 10 francs, you get your choice of rabbit, sausage and potato, pulpo, sardines, chicken, kidney and potato, or shrimp - and some bread with some really good butter. In Old Town, it isn&#39;t easy to find places serving food late, and this places serves at a bargain price for Geneva. I had the shrimp - which were cooked with orange peel, saffron, and summer squash - pretty good. Skip dessert - the tart costs 6 francs and isn&#39;t edible. Most folks are regulars standing around having a drink, and it is hard not to enjoy all the merrymaking.",
