"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0VARTSz-MuNRjcBwNLZD9Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This place had been under construction for awhile and I was eagerly awaiting it to open. It is located in the old town hall right next to the building were you register to get married.  This place finally opened and when I saw inside I was tempted to try it, and I finally got a chance to. The inside is very open, and even has an upstairs area if needed.  This would be a great place to rent for an office event. This is not the place to go for a cheap lunch, the plat du jour would definitely be a good deal here.  However, the plat du jour the day I went was liver, and I can&#39;t do liver.  But, as I had my heart set to eat here, I ordered one of the other menu items.  I had the vegetarian burger, and it was delicious.  I would definitely like to come back to try the other items sometime.  All the other food coming out looked good.  The chocolate molleaux was also delicious. They menu also hosts a wide selection of wines.  The service was friendly and spoke English as well.  Definitely a great place for larger groups.",
