"reviewcomment":"It is always a treat to step into a Globus.  I don&#39;t go often as it is at the high end of the department store and grocery shopping experience in Switzerland, and thus a bit more pricey. I would compare it to a Nordstroms for those from the US.   If I do buy anything it is usually from the supermarket as they have gourmet items that you can&#39;t get at other places.  The store is just beautiful and they do such a great job of how they present everything.  It is just fun to explore and look around.  <br><br>I also really like the food court here for lunch time as they have a variety of items to select from and several benches and tables to sit at.  Just be ready to jump on a place as it can get hectic to find a seat sometimes during the lunch hour.  I have always enjoyed their panini sandwiches here.",
