"rating":"2.0",
"reviewcomment":"Everyone needs a neighborhood baker.  This little bakery doesn&#39;t have a huge variety, but it has a quaint neighborhood feel, and I love that it has an analog cashier machine as well as cozy rustic seating in the back room behind the cashier counter. So I was hoping this would become a regular stop in the morning on my way to work, and perhaps in the evening on my way home for a sweet treat on particularly difficult days. <br><br>So far, I&#39;ve had a croissant and an eclair.  The croissant was fairly standard, neither particularly buttery nor soft.  It was nothing special, but did its job in the morning.  The eclair that I had from here was my first Geneva bakery treat, and perhaps my expectations were too high--when I bit into the eclair, the &#34;cream,&#34; which had more of the texture of a sauce, spilled all over my napkin on the other end of the eclair. <br><br>Considering that there seems to be at least two boulangeries/patiserries on every block, I will have to continue my hunt for a local baker. It&#39;s too bad, too, as aside from the actual food, this place had a lot of unpretentious potential. <br><br>Oh, and apparently they don&#39;t have coffee or drinks. Another minus :-(",
